cff-version: 1.2.0
title: decision-record (idea-to-MVP planning pipeline)
message: >-
  If you use this work and you want to cite it, you can use the metadata
  from this file. Please also cite the upstream canonical decision-record
  concept by Joel Parker Henderson (see "references" below).
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Josh
    family-names: Mabry
    email: josh@protolabs.studio
    affiliation: protoLabs Studio
identifiers:
  - type: url
    value: 'https://github.com/protoLabsAI/decision-record'
    description: This fork — decision-record planning pipeline
repository-code: 'https://github.com/protoLabsAI/decision-record'
abstract: >-
  A Claude Code plugin and MCP server that drives idea-to-MVP planning for
  complex engineering work. It hard-gates a pipeline of phases (intake, scope,
  decisions, task graph, handoff) and refuses to release a plan until every
  decision is accepted and every task is decomposed.
license: MIT
